<TITLE> New education policy soon: Nahid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 17 (bdnews24.com)  The government is set to form a committee soon to draft a national education policy, the education minister said on Tuesday. "We will present a new education policy in a few months," Nurul Islam Nahid said inaugurating a workshop on 'Moral Education in Bangladesh' at the University Grants Commission in Agargaon. The new policy will be drafted in line with the Qudrat-e-Khuda Education Commission report of 1974 and the Shamsul Alam education policy adopted in 2002, he said. "We will also include component of the other education policies adopted by past governments," he said. UNESCO, UGC and the planning ministry jointly organised the workshop. UNESCO's Dhaka director Malama Maalisa presided, UGC chairman Prof Nazrul Islam and attorney general Mahbubey Alam spoke among others. bdne
